# Cache Handling

`CacheView` (`@furystack/shades-common-components`) renders cache state. Subscribes to the observable and handles loading / loaded / obsolete / error automatically.

## Props

| Prop | Type | Required | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `cache` | `Cache<TData, TArgs>` | yes | | the cache instance |
| `args` | `TArgs` | yes | | cache entry key |
| `content` | `ShadeComponent<TContentProps>` | yes | | rendered when value present |
| `contentProps` | `Omit<TContentProps, 'data'>` | yes when content has extra props | | forwarded |
| `loader` | `JSX.Element` | no | `null` | shown when loading and no value yet |
| `error` | `(error, retry) => JSX.Element` | no | default | custom error UI |

## Evaluation order

1. **Error first** — `isFailedCacheResult(result)`: error UI, never content.
2. **Value next** — `hasCacheValue(result)`: render content. Obsolete triggers `cache.reload(...args)` once per cycle.
3. **Loading last** — no value, no error: `loader` or null.

## Usage

```tsx
import { CacheView } from '@furystack/shades-common-components'
import type { CacheWithValue } from '@furystack/cache'

const UserContent = Shade<{ data: CacheWithValue<User> }>({
  customElementName: 'user-content',
  render: ({ props }) => <div>{props.data.value.name}</div>,
})

<CacheView
  cache={userCache}
  args={[userId]}
  content={UserContent}
  loader={<Skeleton />}
  error={(err, retry) => (
    <Alert severity="error" title="Failed to load user">
      <Button onclick={retry}>Retry</Button>
    </Alert>
  )}
/>
```

## Key behaviors

- **Retry**: `cache.reload(...args)` internally; passed to error UI as `retry`. No callback prop needed.
- **Revalidation**: obsolete triggers one `cache.reload(...args)` per obsolete cycle, content keeps rendering with stale value.
- **Args reactivity**: changing `args` re-subscribes to the new cache entry.
- **Type contract**: content receives `CacheWithValue<TData>` — `.value` and `.updatedAt` guaranteed. Check `result.status` to distinguish `'loaded'` vs `'obsolete'`.
- **Custom content props**: pass via `contentProps` when content declares props beyond `data`. TS enforces requirement and types.
